text:
SEC power poll: LSU moves to top spot 
Thu, Oct 8, 2015 @ 9:39 pm | updated Thu, Oct 8, 2015 @ 9:40 pm Photos AP FILE - In this Saturday, Sept. 19, 2015, file photo, Auburn wide receiver D'haquille Williams (1) runs a route for a touchdown reception in the second half of an NCAA college football game against LSU in Baton Rouge, La. Auburn has dismissed senior wide receiver D'haquille Williams from the team, coach Gus Malzahn announced on Monday, Oct. 5, 2015. (AP Photo/Gerald Herbert, File) 
SEC POWER POLL 
Easy win over South Carolina just got easier with game moved to Baton Rouge. 2. TEXAS A&M (5-0) 
Aggies’ defense needs to enjoy bye with Alabama coming to town next week. 3. FLORIDA (5-0) 
Gators have to ride emotional wave to snap two-game losing streak to Missouri. 4. ALABAMA (4-1) 
Crimson Tide may have been down, but they certainly aren’t out. 5. OLE MISS (4-1) 
Lopsided Florida loss means Rebels must win back their respect. 6. GEORGIA (4-1) 
Bulldogs can’t win the big game. Rinse and repeat. 7. MISSOURI (4-1) 
Tigers haven’t seen anything as good as Florida’s swarming defense. 8. MISSISSIPPI STATE (3-2) 
Simply not on the level as others in the West (but who is?) 9. KENTUCKY (4-1) 
Off week before five consecutive conference games that will define season. 10. ARKANSAS (2-3) 
Razorbacks face impossible task of running against Alabama’s front seven. 11. TENNESSEE (2-3) 
Vols blow third double-digit lead and now must face an angry Georgia. 12. AUBURN (3-2) 
With WR Duke Williams (above) off team, Tigers forced into a running game. 13. SOUTH CAROLINA (2-3) 
“Home” game in Louisiana only adds to Gamecocks’ growing misery. 14. VANDERBILT (2-3) 
Team is getting better, but there’s still a long way to go. 
Don Coble , The Times-Union
